<br>
  I have a question.  I am from The Silent Watch.  A guild that can do it's own plane raids.  I know your rules that states that if a guild can manage a plane raid on their own, none of their members are allowed to join the CoG plane raids.<br>
<br>
  But I got a question.  If you guys are doing PoA soon.  Will I be able to just follow you guys to finish my epic?  I will not roll on any items.  I will just finish it and leave or I could stay to help out if you guys want.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for reading this<br>
 <p><b>Goldenmunky Silverback<b><br>
<i>Level 52 Paladin</i><br>
<b>My own momma said I'm dwarfed out<b><br>
<i> Proud member of TSW </i>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoldenmunky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GoldenMunky</A> at: 10/9/01 12:02:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzellex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zellex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sacred Puller of Planes</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/9/01 2:26:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on PoA raid *IF*</span><hr size=1> Rules tend to be a little more slack for PoA.  Most people only raid PoA for epics, other then that tends to be a forgotten plane.<br>
<br>
Now although the planes on CoG was originally founded with the concept of giving small guilds or guildless people a chance to go to the planes without having to join an UBER guild, we can work around this much easier with PoA.<br>
<br>
However, keep in mind although your not rolling on any other items, lotto is all/all.  So any other pallies in your position are eligible to roll.<br>
<br>
Another thing to consider (not trying to discourage you from signing up) The Silent Watch is composed of some very talented people.  I think you can easily schedule this epic on KGC and obtain it without the aid of CoG.<br>
<br>
Zellex <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/9/01 3:17:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on PoA raid *IF*</span><hr size=1> Ummm...what Zellex said.<br>
<br>
Heh.  Yes, the rules are more relaxed for PoA.  And even if they werent, theres no reason you couldnt come along even on a normal CoG plane raid.  Its just that we couldnt have more than a few of you.  But one or two isnt an issue.<br>
<br>
The but part of this is that if we had say 6 Paladins who showed up plus you, we're probably have to seriously look at bumping someone, and the person from a planes capable guild would be first on the block.  Its not that I have anything against you, I dont.  Its just that if cuts have to be made, its better to cut those who might have another chance another day, than someone who might never be able to go again.<br>
<br>
Unfortunatly given the problems wth getting any number of people up to Air, cuts probably would have to be made.  But then again, getting 48 people to agree on staying for a good 3 days in a row is going to be difficult.  So you never know.<br>
<br>
As for when.  I intend to at least attempt this.  Currently I'm putting together a short list of essential people that will need to be there and making sure that we can work out a weekend we can all make it.  Once I have all that down, I'll post something.  Dont expect it anytime soon, however.  Putting something like this together in an organization like CoG isnt easy.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
KCoG Plane Raid Liason<br>
